---
import ShowcaseLayout from "../../layouts/ShowcaseLayout.astro";
import ShowcaseSection from "../../components/ShowcaseSection.astro";
import ContactForm from "../../components/ContactForm.astro";

/*
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  ALL THE CONTENT FOR THIS CASE STUDY LIVES HERE.
  To create a new showcase page, duplicate this file,
  change the props and body text — nothing else needs touching.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
*/
---

<ShowcaseLayout
  title="CRM ↔ Slack Lead Routing"
  description="How we automated lead routing from HubSpot to Slack — zero manual steps, 100% of new deals reach the right rep in seconds."
  service="Automations"
  serviceHref="/automations"
  headline="Zero-Touch Lead Routing from HubSpot to Slack"
  subheadline="New deals automatically reach the right sales rep in the right Slack channel — in under 10 seconds."
  metric1={{ value: "0",    label: "manual steps per lead" }}
  metric2={{ value: "<10s", label: "lead-to-notification time" }}
  metric3={{ value: "100%", label: "routing accuracy" }}
  tags={["HubSpot", "Slack", "Make", "Webhooks"]}
>

  <!--
    PROBLEM SECTION
    Describe the pain the client had before you built the solution.
    Be specific — numbers and quotes are more compelling than generalities.
  -->
  <ShowcaseSection label="The Problem" heading="Deals were falling through the cracks." accent="red">
    <p>
      The client's sales team of eight reps was all in the same Slack channel.
      Every new HubSpot deal triggered a manual copy-paste into Slack — when
      someone remembered to do it. Deals were routed to the wrong rep roughly
      30% of the time, causing delays and occasional lost opportunities.
    </p>
    <p>
      They needed every new deal to instantly reach the right rep based on
      deal value and the rep's assigned region — with no human involvement.
    </p>
  </ShowcaseSection>

  <!--
    SOLUTION SECTION
    Explain what you built. Keep it readable for non-technical stakeholders —
    focus on the outcome, not the internal mechanics.
  -->
  <ShowcaseSection label="The Solution" heading="A Make.com scenario triggered by HubSpot webhooks." accent="brand">
    <p>
      We built a Make.com automation triggered the instant a deal is created
      or moved to "Qualified" in HubSpot. The scenario:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Reads the deal's region and value from HubSpot custom properties.</li>
      <li>Looks up the assigned rep from a routing table (a simple Notion database).</li>
      <li>Posts a formatted Slack message to the rep's personal channel and the regional channel.</li>
      <li>Adds a note to the HubSpot deal confirming the notification was sent.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      The routing table in Notion means the client can update territory
      assignments themselves — no code changes needed.
    </p>
  </ShowcaseSection>

  <!--
    RESULTS SECTION
    Quantify the impact. Even rough numbers ("roughly 3× faster") are better
    than adjectives ("much faster").
  -->
  <ShowcaseSection label="The Results" heading="Every lead reaches the right rep in under 10 seconds." accent="gold">
    <p>
      In the three months since launch, 100% of new qualified deals have been
      routed correctly with zero manual intervention. The client estimates it
      saves the team around 45 minutes per day in copy-paste work and follow-up
      messages to clarify ownership.
    </p>
    <p>
      Two new reps were onboarded by simply adding a row to the Notion routing
      table — no developer required.
    </p>
  </ShowcaseSection>

  <ContactForm
    slot="cta"
    heading="Want Something Like This?"
    subheading="Tell us your workflow and we'll show you how to automate it."
    source="automations-showcase"
  />

</ShowcaseLayout>
